✅ Recommended Approaches
1️⃣ Depth-Standardized Presence via Repeated Rarefaction (Most Robust)

Instead of one subsample, do:

Rarefy each repertoire to the same depth (minimum depth across samples)

Repeat K times (e.g., 100–500)

For each clonotype, compute:

Publicity score
=
fraction of rarefactions where present in ≥ N individuals
Publicity score=fraction of rarefactions where present in ≥ N individuals

Then define:

Public = publicity score ≥ threshold (e.g., 0.9)

Why this works

Equalizes detection probability

Preserves sequence identity

Avoids arbitrary single subsample loss

This is the most principled practical solution.

